		"description": {
			"value": "<p><strong>Action</strong> - 1 Creature (20 ft.) - 1 Charge - Magical</p><p>Holy water only deals damage to &amp;reference[fiend] or &amp;reference[undead] creature. The DC for holy water equals 8 + your proficiency bonus + dexterity modifier.</p><p><strong>[[/save dexterity]]{Dexterity Save}</strong></p><ul><li><p><strong>Failure:</strong> [[/damage 4d6 radiant]] damage.</p></li><li><p><strong>Success:</strong> Half damage.</p></li></ul><p></p><p><em>Diluting holy water diminishes its effectiveness. If there is less than 0.2 pounds of @UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-spells.Item.fnmCUzOkiNZDOpQ0]{holy silver and iron powder} per pound of water, the water deals less damage, proportional to the reduced ratio. Holy water cannot be concentrated to deal more damage.</em></p>",
